                        <div class="editorBody">
                                <div class="nameGroup">
                                        <h3>Prof. Simon D.M. White </h3>
                                        <p>Max-Planck-Institut für Astrophysik, Germany </p>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="details">
                                            <p><strong>Biography</strong></p>

<p>Born in the UK, Simon White has worked since 1994 at the Max Planck Institute for Astrophysics in Garching, near Munich. He is interested in the growth and statistical properties of cosmic structure, the formation, evolution and clustering of galaxies, and the nature and distribution of dark matter. He has pioneered many aspects of the use of numerical simulations to study these topics.</p>
 
                                            
                                                                                       
                                                <p><a href="https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1061-6154"><img alt="ORCID logo" src="https://orcid.org/sites/default/files/images/orcid_16x16.png">https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1061-6154</a></p>
                                            
